________________________________ ________________________________ ________________________________ ________________________________ ________________________________ Hardtack: Mix 4 cups of flour (preferably whole wheat) with 4 teaspoons of salt.
Add just enough water (a little less than 2 cups) to make the mixture stick together.
Roll dough out 1/2 inch thick and shape it into a rough rectangle.
Cut the dough into 3x3 inch squares.
Make four rows of depressions in the dough on both sides (it should look much like a saltine cracker).
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and put into 375 degree oven for 30 minutes.
Flip over each cracker and bake for another 30 minutes.
Please write a few words that say what it was like to be a citizen soldier in a war.
